{
  "name": "Bookings",
  "description": "Customer-facing booking flow (Sprint B3.1–B3.3). The webhook surface for `checkout.session.completed` lands in B3.4 — for now, **created bookings stay PENDING after Stripe payment** because no webhook listener writes back yet.\n\n**Pre-conditions:**\n1. `tourSlug` points at a published tour (run `Tours (Admin) → POST /admin/tours` and set `isPublished=true`, or rely on the seed catalog).\n2. The target tour has at least one OPEN departure with seats available. Easiest: run the Postman folder cycle in `Tours (Admin) — Departures` so `{{departureId}}` is set.\n3. Caller is signed in as a customer (`/auth/sync` already ran). The folder uses the customer JWT slot automatically.\n\nThe POST captures `{{bookingCode}}` for the follow-up GET requests.",
  "event": [
    {
      "listen": "prerequest",
      "script": {
        "type": "text/javascript",
        "exec": [
          "// Self-sufficient: fetch an OPEN departure with enough free seats for",
          "// this booking (2 adults + 1 child = 3) and pin it as {{departureId}}.",
          "// This decouples Bookings from the Departures (Admin) folder, which",
          "// creates → closes → DELETES its own departure and would otherwise",
          "// leave {{departureId}} unset by the time we reach this request.",
          "const slug = pm.environment.get('tourSlug');",
          "if (!slug) { console.warn('[bookings] tourSlug missing'); return; }",
          "const REQUIRED_SEATS = 3;",
          "pm.sendRequest({",
          "  url: pm.environment.get('baseUrl') + '/tours/' + slug + '/departures',",
          "  method: 'GET',",
          "}, (err, res) => {",
          "  if (err) { console.warn('[bookings] departure fetch failed', err); return; }",
          "  const list = (res.json().data || []);",
          "  // Prefer the OPEN departure with the most free seats.",
          "  const open = list",
          "    .filter((d) => d.status === 'OPEN' && (d.seatsTotal - d.seatsBooked) >= REQUIRED_SEATS)",
          "    .sort((a, b) => (b.seatsTotal - b.seatsBooked) - (a.seatsTotal - a.seatsBooked));",
          "  if (open.length) { pm.environment.set('departureId', open[0].id); }",
          "  else { console.warn('[bookings] no OPEN departure with >= ' + REQUIRED_SEATS + ' free seats for ' + slug); }",
          "});"
        ]
      }
    }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "POST /bookings (create + Stripe Checkout session)",
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
        "body": {
          "mode": "raw",
          "raw": "{\n  \"tourSlug\": \"{{tourSlug}}\",\n  \"departureId\": \"{{departureId}}\",\n  \"numAdults\": 2,\n  \"numChildren\": 1,\n  \"contactName\": \"Test Customer\",\n  \"contactEmail\": \"customer@example.com\",\n  \"contactPhone\": \"+84901234567\",\n  \"specialRequests\": \"Vegetarian meals for one adult.\"\n}"
        },
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/bookings",
          "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
          "path": ["bookings"]
        },
        "description": "Creates a PENDING booking and mints a Stripe Checkout session.\n\n**Response:**\n- 201 `{ data: { bookingId, bookingCode, checkoutUrl, status: 'PENDING' } }`\n- 400 `DEPARTURE_NOT_OPEN` — departure is CLOSED/CANCELLED\n- 401 `USER_NOT_SYNCED` — call `/auth/sync` first\n- 404 `TOUR_NOT_FOUND` | `DEPARTURE_NOT_FOUND`\n- 409 `SEATS_NOT_AVAILABLE` — best-effort capacity check failed\n\nOpen `checkoutUrl` in a browser to test the Stripe flow. Use test card `4242 4242 4242 4242` with any future expiry + any 3-digit CVC. The booking stays PENDING until B3.4 webhook lands."
      },
      "response": [
        {
          "name": "201 Created",
          "originalRequest": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [],
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/bookings", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["bookings"] }
          },
          "status": "Created",
          "code": 201,
          "_postman_previewlanguage": "json",
          "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
          "body": "{\n  \"data\": {\n    \"bookingId\": \"3fa85f64-5717-4562-b3fc-2c963f66afa6\",\n    \"bookingCode\": \"BK-ABC12345\",\n    \"checkoutUrl\": \"https://checkout.stripe.com/c/pay/cs_test_...\",\n    \"status\": \"PENDING\"\n  },\n  \"error\": null\n}"
        },
        {
          "name": "409 SEATS_NOT_AVAILABLE",
          "originalRequest": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [],
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/bookings", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["bookings"] }
          },
          "status": "Conflict",
          "code": 409,
          "_postman_previewlanguage": "json",
          "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
          "body": "{\n  \"data\": null,\n  \"error\": { \"code\": \"SEATS_NOT_AVAILABLE\", \"message\": \"Only 1 seat(s) left, requested 3\" }\n}"
        }
      ],
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "pm.test('status is 201', () => pm.response.to.have.status(201));",
              "const body = pm.response.json();",
              "if (pm.response.code === 201 && body.data) {",
              "  pm.test('returns checkout envelope', () => {",
              "    pm.expect(body.data.bookingCode).to.match(/^BK-/);",
              "    pm.expect(body.data.checkoutUrl).to.match(/^https:\\/\\/checkout\\.stripe\\.com\\//);",
              "    pm.expect(body.data.status).to.eql('PENDING');",
              "  });",
              "  pm.environment.set('bookingCode', body.data.bookingCode);",
              "  pm.environment.set('bookingId', body.data.bookingId);",
              "  console.log('Open this in a browser to test Stripe:', body.data.checkoutUrl);",
              "}"
            ]
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "GET /bookings/me (own list)",
      "request": {
        "method": "GET",
        "header": [],
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/bookings/me",
          "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
          "path": ["bookings", "me"]
        },
        "description": "Lists the caller's bookings, newest first (max 50). Includes parent tour + departure summary so the FE can render the list without a follow-up join."
      },
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "pm.test('status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
              "const body = pm.response.json();",
              "pm.test('returns an array', () => pm.expect(body.data).to.be.an('array'));",
              "if (body.data.length > 0) {",
              "  pm.test('newest first', () => {",
              "    const dates = body.data.map((b) => b.createdAt);",
              "    const sorted = dates.slice().sort().reverse();",
              "    pm.expect(dates).to.eql(sorted);",
              "  });",
              "}"
            ]
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "GET /bookings/:code (detail)",
      "request": {
        "method": "GET",
        "header": [],
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/bookings/{{bookingCode}}",
          "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
          "path": ["bookings", "{{bookingCode}}"]
        },
        "description": "Owner-or-admin only. Non-owner customers see the same `404 BOOKING_NOT_FOUND` as a truly-missing code — we don't leak code existence to enumeration attacks."
      },
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "pm.test('status is 200 or 404', () => pm.expect([200, 404]).to.include(pm.response.code));",
              "const body = pm.response.json();",
              "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
              "  pm.test('returns booking with tour + departure joined', () => {",
              "    pm.expect(body.data.code).to.match(/^BK-/);",
              "    pm.expect(body.data.tour).to.be.an('object');",
              "    pm.expect(body.data.departure).to.be.an('object');",
              "  });",
              "} else {",
              "  pm.test('error code is BOOKING_NOT_FOUND', () => pm.expect(body.error.code).to.eql('BOOKING_NOT_FOUND'));",
              "}"
            ]
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
